in Phnom Penh during the Cambodian Civil War, a booby-trap bomb exploded in his car. Two others were killed; Enders escaped injury."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Built the IEA as a counterweight to OPEC","body":"As Henry Kissinger's pick for Assistant Secretary for Economic Affairs, Enders spearheaded the International Energy Agency — still operating today as a counterbalance to OPEC — coordinating Western energy policy after the 1973 oil crisis."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Ambassador who laid groundwork for CUSFTA","body":"As US Ambassador to Canada 1976-1979, Enders made free trade the centerpiece of his mission, travelling 50,000 miles annually across the country. The Canadian-US Free Trade Agreement his work helped make possible came into force in 1989."},{"number":4,"category":"politics","header":"Denied El Mozote massacre before the Senate","body":"In 1982, testifying before a Senate committee, Enders disputed New York Times and Washington Post reports on the El Mozote massacre in El Salvador, in which the Salvadoran Army killed more than 800 civilians. He stated no evidence could be found of a systematic massacre — a position later contradicted by forensic evidence."}],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Thomas O. Enders","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_O._Enders"}],"artworks":[],"documents":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"cross_connections":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Thomas","middle_name":"Ostrom","last_name":"Enders","married_names":[],"display_name":"Thomas Ostrom Enders","photo_url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/04/ThomasOEnders.jpg","photo_notes":"Official diplomatic portrait. Wikimedia Commons."},"military_service":[],"slug":"thomas-enders-1931"},"I00182":{"id":"I00182","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1933,"month":12,"day":20,"city":"Tangier","state":"Tanger-Tetouan-